name: The Laramie Project
description: Audible presents the 25th anniversary concert reading of The Laramie Project, the revolutionary play that shook America's conscience. In 1998, a 21-year-old gay man named Matthew Shepard was kidnapped and murdered just outside the college town of Laramie, Wyoming. Following the tragedy, members of Tectonic Theater Project wove together over 200 authentic voices from the community in a powerful tapestry of grief, reflection, and ultimately, hope. Now, Tony and Pulitzer Prize nominee Moisés Kaufman, Artistic Director of Tectonic Theater Project, revisits thislandmark work-hailed as one of the most vital in the American theatre canon-at Audible's Minetta Lane Theatre. Don't miss the strictly limited run of this groundbreaking theatrical event. *Casting is subject to change

description:
Why buy gifts when you can make them?

Every Saturday and Sunday from now until December 28th, unleash your inner street artist at our Holiday Rebel Stencil Class 

at 1 PM and create one-of-a-kind holiday gifts that are anything but ordinary.
Make your own Banksy-inspired art for everyone on your list — bold, creative, and totally unique.
After class, the museum is yours — wander, snap photos, and soak up the creativity as long as you like!

1–3 PM Stencil Class • Stay as long as you like 
Spots fill fast — grab yours now and make your weekend a work of art!

NOW ALSO OFFERING: Weekend Guided Tour and Stencil Class Combo! Make it a full day with both our Stencil Class and our Guided Tour plus entrance to the museum!

Explore iconic works, rare installations, and rebellious social commentary. Perfect for families, art lovers, and free thinkers alike. Challenge the norm, spark conversation, and see street art like never before.

name: Banksy Museum NY - HOLIDAY STENCIL WORKSHOP
description:

name: Candy Crafting at Cricket's Candy Creations
description:
Cricket’s Candy Creations is a multi-sensory experience where creators of all ages can craft edible candy art while immersed in a variety of candy-themed activities designed to be a unique outlet for exploration, visualization, creativity, and fun! Creators make uniquely delicious crafts such as Edible Slime, Candy Jewelry, Lickable Fingerpaint, and more!

*Exact crafts may vary due to ongoing supply challenges. We appreciate your understanding!
*Tickets must be purchased in advance.

Price: $65 General Admission
*General admission for 1 person includes entry PLUS all five of your candy creations! Experience lasts about 50 minutes.

Price: $80 "Cherry on Top"
*Our “Cherry on Top” VIP experience includes a special tote bag decorating session (plus aprons for kids!) and cotton candy making!  Experience last about 60 minutes.

Seasonal Themes Include:October: Halloween
November: Fall/Autumn 
December: Winter Holidays 

Children 16 and under must be accompanied by an adult. 

We Support Learning Through Play! Cricket's Candy Creations believe that learning through play can help bridge some of these gaps and inspire kids and families to engage in the world around them. That's why Cricket's Candy Creations is a proud supporter of The Association of Children’s Museums and the work of its members to ensure a healthy start in life—physically, emotionally, socially, and intellectually — for all children.


Your session starts PROMPTLY at the ticketed time. Please arrive 10 minutes early for General Admission tickets and 15 minutes early for Cherry on Top tickets . We will do our best to accommodate any late-comers by adding them to a session already in progress.

Tickets are non-refundable.
All activities are subject to change without notice. Please email info@cricketcandy.com for the current activities.

name: Rougui
description: Rougui is a renowned Guinean singer and songwriter celebrated for her powerful voice, captivating compositions, and dynamic stage presence. With over a decade of musical training and performance across Africa and Europe, she has carved a unique space in Guineas vibrant music scene.Her journey is as compelling as her artistry: forced to leave her homeland at a young age, Rougui endured a five-year odyssey through Mali, Mauritania, Morocco, and back to Guinea before finally reaching France. This harrowing experience of clandestine migration deeply shaped her music, making her a powerful voice for resilience, identity, and hope. Known for her ability to improvise and blend traditional Guinean rhythms with modern Afro-pop and soul influences.Now, presented by **Show Mondial**, she brings her live band to New York City for the very first time. Performances also from, Ousmane Diabate, Zaga Boy, American Boys.

name: Emmet Cohen Trio
description: Emmet Cohen (piano), Yasushi Nakamura (Bass) and Joe Farnsworth (drums)Multifaceted American jazz pianist and composer Emmet Cohen is one of his generations pivotal figures in music and the related arts. Leader of the Emmet Cohen Trio and creator of the Masters Legacy Series, he is an internationally acclaimed jazz artist, a dedicated educator, the winner of the 2019 American Pianists Awards, and a finalist in the 2011 Thelonious Monk International Piano Competition. Cohen headlines regularly at Jazz at Lincoln Center, the Village Vanguard, and Birdland, and has appeared at the Newport, Monterey, and North Sea jazz festivals. His artistry has taken him to venues and festivals in over 30 countries. Cohens entrepreneurial energies led to his developing Live From Emmets Place, a live-streamed Harlem rent party that unites a worldwide audience via tens of millions of internet views. Cohen has released over ten albums as leader and has performed or recorded with Ron Carter, Benny Golson, Jimmy Cobb, George Coleman, Jimmy Heath, Tootie Heath, Houston Person, Christian McBride, and Kurt Elling.

name: Emmet Cohen Trio
description: Emmet Cohen (piano), Yasushi Nakamura (Bass) and Joe Farnsworth (drums)Multifaceted American jazz pianist and composer Emmet Cohen is one of his generations pivotal figures in music and the related arts. Leader of the Emmet Cohen Trio and creator of the Masters Legacy Series, he is an internationally acclaimed jazz artist, a dedicated educator, the winner of the 2019 American Pianists Awards, and a finalist in the 2011 Thelonious Monk International Piano Competition. Cohen headlines regularly at Jazz at Lincoln Center, the Village Vanguard, and Birdland, and has appeared at the Newport, Monterey, and North Sea jazz festivals. His artistry has taken him to venues and festivals in over 30 countries. Cohens entrepreneurial energies led to his developing Live From Emmets Place, a live-streamed Harlem rent party that unites a worldwide audience via tens of millions of internet views. Cohen has released over ten albums as leader and has performed or recorded with Ron Carter, Benny Golson, Jimmy Cobb, George Coleman, Jimmy Heath, Tootie Heath, Houston Person, Christian McBride, and Kurt Elling.

description: Every Friday, and for two headlining weeks a year, the BBB roars into action playing a thrilling and original mix of jazz, funk, Brazilian, Latin and world music for sold-out audiences. name: Richard II
description: Run Time: Approximately 2 hours and 30 minutes, including a 15-minute intermission. Age Recommendation: Richard II is intended for ages 8 and up. Children under 5 are not permitted. All guests must have a ticket. Richard II contains brief nudity, gunshots, and fog/haze effects. When is a king, a king no more? Ambition and betrayal reign supreme in this electrifying reimagining of Shakespeare's poetic masterpiece. Set in 1980s Manhattan, the neon skyline and shadowy backrooms become an epic battleground of identity and power, where a king's divine right crumbles beneath the weight of human frailty. Michael Urie's virtuosic performance and Craig Baldwin's inventive adaptation make Richard's tragic descent freshly immediate, staged a stone's throw from the site of the historic Astor Place Riots, the original American cocktail of politics, insurrection, and Shakespeare.
